What a nice alternative to the chain sandwich shops! Was my first time here and they do mostly Italian sandwiches and they do them well. Nothing fancy, but the meats were quality and the bread was excellent - not too thick, nice and chewy. The standard 8 inch was more than enough for me (I'm a big guy) and my wife and I probably could have split a 12 inch and been fine (but I have to admit, it was so good I am glad I had this extra couple of bites!) I'm so glad we found this place. It's going on our list of regular spots.

I did love their quality until a more recent experience since COVID. The manager/owner is rude.  Although I noticed that in the past, I still patronized because of the quality and the subologists (Yes, I did). I witnessed her speak to one of the employees, in front of customers in such a demeaning way, I felt so bad for the individual and hung my head down.  Back to the recent experience. This particular day, it was a total of three people in the establishment and we all had on masks. I was standing near the counter and the manager/owner remarks about the proximity and stated anyone who ordered must move from the counter area. Minutes later, two men, extremely disheveled, walked in with no masks.  The manager/owner greeted them (never greeted me nor the person accompanying me which was a regular), never told them to put on a mask, and ALLOWED them to stand directly in front of the area of the counter where they create the subs.  Done. Would give ZERO stars.
